-- Capello Will Pick Newcastle Striker Carroll, Mirror Says: Soccer Roundup
-- B y   A l e x   D u f f
-- 2010-10-01T10:25:50Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-01/capello-will-pick-newcastle-striker-carroll-mirror-says-soccer-roundup.html
The following is a roundup of soccer
stories from U.K. newspapers, with clickable links to the Web.  Carroll for England  England coach Fabio Capello is set to pick Newcastle
striker Andy Carroll for a European 2012 qualifier against
Montenegro, the  Daily Mirror  reported.  Capello will call up the 21-year-old forward next week
after he was left out of England’s Under-21 squad, the Mirror
said. Jermain Defoe and Bobby Zamora aren’t available and there
are doubts over Wayne Rooney, according to the newspaper.  Rooney Will Make It  Manchester United coach Alex Ferguson said Wayne Rooney
should be fit to play for England in the match,  the Guardian 
reported.  Rooney is likely to be “100 percent” by the time of the
Oct. 12 qualifier, the newspaper quoted Ferguson as saying.  Chelsea Eyes Mexes  Chelsea may try to sign Roma’s Philippe Mexes in the
January transfer window, the  Daily Mail  reported.  The France centerback is free to talk to foreign clubs from
Jan. 1 because his contract with the Serie A club expires after
the season, according to the Mail.  Wigan to Marseille  Charles N’Zogbia wants to leave Wigan for Marseille, the
 Daily Mail  reported.  The 24-year-old, whose 9 million pound ($14.3 million) move
to Birmingham collapsed in August over his personal terms, said
Wigan is a “springboard” for him, according to the Mail.  To contact the reporter on this story:
